The objective of parameter optimization is to modify the values of the parameters so as to minimize the error function, S, Eq. (13), representing the square of the differences between the values of reference data, Qref(i), and the values calculated using the semiempirical method, Qcalc(i), with appropriate weighting factors, gi.
